OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAfter a chilly start, Friday
OL,6,Fwill be mostly dry with some bright or
OL,7,Fsunny spells. A few, mostly light,
OL,8,Fshowers are possible through the
OL,9,Fafternoon. With winds steadily easing
OL,10,Fit will feel a little less chilly too.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FThe odd light coastal shower
OL,13,Fis possible overnight. Otherwise, dry
OL,14,Fwith clear spells and light winds.
OL,15,FThis will allow temperatures to fall
OL,16,Faway and a patchy frost to form.
OL,17,
OL,18,CSaturday:FA dry, bright and chilly
OL,19,Fstart. Remaining mostly dry with cloud
OL,20,Fincreasing from the west. Some light
OL,21,Frain is possible by evening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
